This paper is about learning-to-rank algorithms for search systems, which is a topic that falls under information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses techniques for reducing bias in click data, which is a problem that is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR, followed by cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, and cs.DS.
